<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-09-28T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-09-28T16:00:00-05:00" n="818" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d818">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.252/64: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-09-28T17:00:00-04:00">September 28, 1931—5
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 5:50 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>121. Department’s telegram No. 45, September 28, noon. <hi rend="italic">Modus vivendi</hi> signed this afternoon. The Foreign Office
                            insisted upon 15 days’ cancellation clause since agreement with France
                            contains this provision.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>